<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>Checkout Notification</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      background-color: #f5f5f5;
    }
    .head-con {
      width: 100%;
      height: 50px;
      background-color: green;
      color: white;
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: center;
    }
    .email-body {
      padding: 20px;
      max-width: 600px;
      margin: 20px auto;
      background-color: white;
      border-radius: 5px;
      box-shadow: 0 0 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
    }
    h2 {
      color: #333;
    }
    p {
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #555;
    }
    .footer {
      margin-top: 20px;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: #888;
      text-align: center;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <header>
    <div class="head-con">
      <h2>Thriftify</h2>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="email-body">
    <h2>Hello {{name}},</h2>
    <p>
      Weâ€™re excited to let you know that your item <strong>{{itemname}}</strong> is currently being checked out by a buyer.
    </p>
    <p>
      You will be notified as soon as the payment is confirmed and the buyer completes their checkout process.
    </p>
    <p>
      Please ensure the item remains available and ready for dispatch, pending confirmation.
    </p>
    <p>
      Thank you for using Thriftify, and we appreciate your trust in our platform.
    </p>

    <p>
      Kind regards,<br/>
      The Thriftify Team
    </p>

    <div class="footer">
      &copy; {{year}} Thriftify. All rights reserved.
    </div>
  </div>

</body>
</html>
